e bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud Dunstroke was born about 1161, in Surrey, England, United Kingdom. She married William Cobham about 1253, in Kent, England. They were the parents of at least 3 daughters."},"et":{"ABT 1161–Deceased":"umbes 1161–Surnud","1223–1265":"1223–1265","1254–Female":"1254–Surnud","1256–Female":"1256–Surnud","1258–1337":"1258–1337","1161–Female":"1161–Surnud","ABT 1161":"umbes 1161","1337":"1337","1258":"1258","1256":"1256","1223":"1223","1254":"1254","1265":"1265","1161":"1161","Of Surrey, England":"Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1161–Deceased":"noin 1161–Kuollut","1223–1265":"1223–1265","1254–Female":"1254–Kuollut","1256–Female":"1256–Kuollut","1258–1337":"1258–1337","1161–Female":"1161–Kuollut","ABT 1161":"noin 1161","1337":"1337","1258":"1258","1256":"1256","1223":"1223","1254":"1254","1265":"1265","1161":"1161","Of Surrey, England":"Surrey, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1161–Deceased":"environ 1161–Décédée","1223–1265":"1223–1265","1254–Female":"1254–Décédée","1256–Female":"1256–Décédée","1258–1337":"1258–1337","1161–Female":"1161–Décédée","ABT 1161":"environ 1161","1337":"1337","1258":"1258","1256":"1256","1223":"1223","1254":"1254","1265":"1265","1161":"1161","Of Surrey, England":"Surrey, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Maud Dunstroke est née environ 1161, à Surrey, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé William Cobham environ 1253, à Kent, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 3 filles."},"de":{"ABT 1161–Deceased":"um 1161–Verstorben","1223–1265":"1223–1265","1254–Female":"1254–Verstorben","1256–Female":"1256–Verstorben","1258–1337":"1258–1337","1161–Female":"1161–Verstorben","ABT 1161":"um 1161","1337":"1337","1258":"1258","1256":"1256","1223":"